results.story: Made for big kids, the Under Armour Embiid One GS ‘Origin’ treats Joel Embiid’s debut signature shoe to a lightweight build suitable for the guard position. The breathable black mesh upper, accented with red and yellow TPU wings for midfoot stability, rides on a midsole that blends Under Armour’s UA HOVR and Micro G cushioning technologies. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features radiating lines that trace the shapes of Africa and North America, offering visual cues of Joel’s journey to the NBA.

results.story: The Curry 7 Big Kids 'Chinese New Year' features a festive colorway meant to honor guóhuà, a classic style of Chinese painting. A pink and green floral print adorns the heel panel, contrasting the varying shades of grey used throughout the upper. A metallic gold flexible plate adds an additional pop of color while also separating the sneaker’s UA HOVR and Micro G cushioning technologies, which combine to enhance sharp cuts and an explosive first step.

results.story: The Under Armour Project Rock 2 GS 'Blood Orange' is a kids' sized take on Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson's signature shoe. The shoe features a brightly hued, anatomically informed knit upper highlighted with metallic gold logos. On the medial, the pro wrestler, actor and producer's mantra—'BLOOD. SWEAT. RESPECT.'—is debossed for inspiration. This June 2019 edition improves on its predecessor with Energy Web, HOVR and Tribase technology for of-the-moment training comfort.

Under Armour Curry 6 International Boulevard (GS)
Under Armour Curry 6 Dub Nation (GS)
results.story: The Under Armour Curry 6 GS sneaker runs the game with modern upgrades and a unique design. Paying homage to the Warriors, this 'Dub Nation' kids' version—debuted in April 2019—creates a compression-like fit across the foot with widespread laces and an integrated tongue. The threaded external heel stabilizes the counter while a honeycomb print on the midsole adds stylish distinction. UA HOVR cushioning and a split rubber outsole live below to enhance court contact.

results.name: Under Armour Curry 6 Splash Party (GS)
results.story: Featuring a Warriors-inspired Petrol Blue and Mod Grey knit upper, the Under Armour Curry 6 GS 'Splash Party' sneaker is a kids’ edition of Stephen Curry’s sixth signature shoe. Originally released on March 14, 2019, to celebrate the star point guard’s 31st birthday, the design features a knit upper that’s reinforced by a vibrant pink lacing system that wraps around the heel. The pink-speckled midsole emblazoned with a matching SC30 logo symbolizes the confetti that rains down over the streets of Oakland during the team’s championship parades.

results.name: Under Armour Curry 6 Coy Fish (GS)
results.colorway: High Vis Yellow/High Vis Yellow-Guardian Green
results.story: The Under Armour Curry 6 GS 'Coy Fish' sneaker is a kids’ edition of the adult model released for 2019 All-Star Weekend. Influenced by the star point guard’s prankster personality, this biographical-inspired shoe translates an early, college-day prank into a bold, eye-catching design. While celebrating his 21st birthday at a Japanese steak house, his teammates devised a plan to catch a koi from the fish pond. A security camera caught the action and the team greeted restaurant patrons as discipline. This striking colorway is a nod to Curry’s mischievous spirit—with a High Vis Yellow hue dressing the knit upper and a full-length HOVR midsole reinforcing the water-like clear outsole.

results.name: Under Armour Curry 6 Working on Excellence (GS)
results.story: Styled for growing feet, the Under Armour Curry 6 GS 'Working on Excellence' is a kids’ version of the monochromatic model that debuted in February 2019. Designed as an homage to GSW point guard, Stephen Curry’s unrelenting work ethic, the black-and-white knit scheme represents the athlete’s work balance between his family and on the court. The adapted design features the same best-in-class split outsole traction of the adult version which keeps Curry gripped to the floor during his lightning quick moves.

results.name: Under Armour Curry 6 Underrated (GS)
results.story: Done up in the navy and orange hues of the Warriors’ original uniforms, the Under Armour Curry 6 GS ‘Underrated’ takes its name from the way Steph Curry’s skills were perennially overlooked during his early career. Performance features include a lightweight and breathable mesh upper and lightweight UA HOVR cushioning, featuring a soft foam core enveloped in a net-like energy web.

results.name: Under Armour Curry 6 Heart Of The Town (GS)
results.story: Celebrating the Golden State Warriors’ East Bay hometown of Oakland, the Under Armour Curry 6 GS ‘Heart of the Town’ features a brilliant monochromatic red finish saturated into its mesh upper. The crimson hue extends to the shoe’s full-length UA HOVR cushioned midsole, supported underfoot by a unique split outsole designed to promote both flexibility and traction.

results.name: Under Armour Curry 6 Fox Theatre (GS)
results.story: In tribute to one of Oakland’s most iconic landmarks, the Under Armour Curry 6 GS 'Fox Theater' sneaker pays homage to the historic Fox Theater which hosted the global launch of Stephen Curry’s signature shoe. This January 2019 kids' edition features a Black knit upper accented by vibrant neon hits of Orange and Yellow throughout—a nod to the theater’s marquee sign. A full-length HOVR midsole reinforced by a split outsole design and a unique tread pattern deliver the superior traction the athlete requires for lightning quick cuts on the court.
